headline: This Nuclear Play Trades at 61% Premium Despite Earnings Falling 22% This Quarter
summary: Constellation Energy (Nasdaq: CEG) and NextEra Energy (NYSE: NEE) both missed Q3 2025 revenue expectations, but the stories reveal fundamentally different business models competing for the AI-driven energy boom. Nuclear Focus vs. Diversified Balance Constellation posted $6.57 billion in revenue and $3.04 per share in adjusted earnings, both below Wall Street targets. CEO Joe Dominguez ...
